methods.javadoc: Combines value with any previously saved future register value at address or any value stored in the program if there is no previously saved future value. Use this method when multiple flows to the same address don't matter or the flowing from address is unknown. When value has conflicting bits with the previously saved value, value will take precedence. If the register value is the value for the processor context register and a previously saved value does not exist, the user saved values in the stored context of the program will be used as existing value. @param address the address to store the register value @param value the register value to store at the address
methods.name: setFutureRegisterValue
methods.comment:
Combines value with any previously saved future
 register value at address or any value stored in the program if there is no
 previously saved future value.  Use this method when multiple flows to the same address
 don't matter or the flowing from address is unknown.
 
 When value has conflicting bits with the previously
 saved value, value will take precedence.
  
 If the register value is the value for the 
 processor context register and a previously saved
 value does not exist, the user saved values in the 
 stored context of the program will be used as existing
 value.

params.name: address
params.comment: the address to store the register value

params.name: value
params.comment: the register value to store at the address
